# Per-Dockerfile ignore for docbackend/Dockerfile. BuildKit picks this up
# when the Dockerfile path is docbackend/Dockerfile and uses it INSTEAD of
# the repo-root .dockerignore.
#
# Why we need our own:
#   - The root .dockerignore excludes `doc/` (the main mimo2codex npm package
#     ships docs via `files` whitelist, not via docker context).
#   - docbackend's image specifically `COPY doc /app/doc` so the AI assistant
#     has the markdown corpus — we MUST NOT exclude `doc/` here.

# Heavy / irrelevant directories
.git
.github
.claude
.codex
.idea
.vscode
node_modules

# Other workspaces — docbackend doesn't need them
docweb
web
dist
mimoskill
tutorial-video

# Test data and large media
test
images

# Per-platform / generated files
*.tgz
package-lock.json
yarn.lock
pnpm-lock.yaml
.DS_Store
*.log

# docbackend's own build artifacts (the binary is produced inside the
# builder stage from go.mod / cmd / internal — we don't want a host-built
# bin/ to override that)
docbackend/bin
docbackend/*.exe
docbackend/*.log
